    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Fragment b: <bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1930"/>, p. 172, n. <citedRange>6</citedRange> (ph.)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.88</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioTacc"/>, <citedRange>XX.33</citedRange></bibl>, whence again
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>136</citedRange></bibl> as unpublished;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#marengo1985"/><citedRange/></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>36.1461</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>018200</citedRange></bibl>.</p> 
                   <p>Unpublished fragment a joined with fragment b: <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>018200</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἀριστώνυμος"><milestone unit="fragment" n="a"/>Ἀρισ<supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied><milestone unit="fragment" n="b"/>ώνυμος</name> 
                        <g type="punct">⋮</g> <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Τ_" type="patronymic"><seg part="I">Τ</seg></name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></persName></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><milestone unit="fragment" n="a"/>τῶ<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied>  <persName type="divine" ref="#Apollo"><name nymRef="#Ἀπόλλων"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied><milestone unit="fragment" n="b"/>πόλλωνι</name></persName> <g type="punct">⋮</g> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p>
                    <app loc="1">
                        <lem>᾿Αρισ<supplied reason="lost">τ</supplied>ώνυμος</lem>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1930"><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65685"><name><supplied reason="lost">Σ</supplied>ώνυμος</name></persName> <note>without knowing the initial fragment</note></rdg>
                        <rdg resp="#SECir"><supplied reason="lost">Εὐ</supplied>ώνυμος <note>without knowing the initial fragment</note></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <app loc="2">
                        <lem>τῶ<supplied reason="lost">ι Ἀ</supplied>πόλλωνι ⋮ <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></lem>
                        <rdg resp="#oliverio1930"><supplied reason="lost">Ἀ</supplied>πόλλωνι ⋮ <supplied reason="lost">δεκάταν</supplied></rdg>
                    </app>
                </p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aris<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>ônumos fils de T<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré</supplied> à <supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>pollon <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aris<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>onymos son of T<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated</supplied> to <supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>pollo <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Aris<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied>onymos figlio di T<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato</supplied> ad <supplied reason="lost">A</supplied>pollo <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The missing word at end might be either <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀνέθηκε</foreign> "dedicated" or <foreign xml:lang="grc">δεκάταν</foreign> "as a tithe", which was
                    preferred by <bibl><ptr target="#oliverio1930"/></bibl>, but is not unescapable. In fact the squeeze shows a very tiny part of the upper angle
                of a letter that might be either an alpha or a delta; this cannot help to decide between the two possibilities.</p>
                <p>With a very careful layout the tripuncts of lines 1 and 2 are strictly corresponding to each other. Consequently the father's name was 7 characters long, whichever 
                    the word lost at line 2.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
